<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Ravish" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ravish,</orth> 1) to rob, to carry away by force: <cit><quote>the --ed Helen,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 4.1.24" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 1, 24</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>these hairs which thou dost r. from my chin,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 3.7.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 7, 38</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to deflower by violence; absol.: <cit><quote>with Tarquin's --ing strides,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 2.1.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 1, 55</bibl></cit>. Trans.: Lucr. Arg. <bibl n="shak. mac 2.1.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 1, 55</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 78</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.8.31" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 8, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.337" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 3, 337</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 4.6.81" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. IV, 6, 81</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.4.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 4, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.1.53" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.1.92" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 92</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.1.92" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 92</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 5.3.53" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.3.53" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 53</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tit 5.3.53" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 53</bibl> <bibl n="shak. cym 3.5.142" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 5, 142</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.1.103" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 1, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.6.5" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 6, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.6.5" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 6, 5</bibl> Metaphorically, == to pollute (?): <cit><quote>with rotten damps r. the morning air,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 778" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 778</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) to enchant, to transport; absol.: <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.1.211" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 1, 211</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.32" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 32</bibl>. Trans.: <bibl n="shak. pp 108" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 108</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.168" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 168</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 2.75.168" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.260" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 260</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.260" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 260</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.5.15" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 5, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.2.120" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 2, 120</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>